"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Low power (left panel) and high power (right panel) photomicrographs of inverted papillomas, which usually arise from the lateral nasal wall or paranasal sinuses. They may be entirely endophytic, or they may also have an exophytic component. In contrast to fungiform papillomas, they have malignant potential. Despite differences in behavior, fungiform and inverted papillomas have a similar lining, consisting of nonkeratinized squamous, mucinous and surface ciliated cells. Note the characteristic microabcesses (black arrow, right panel).",
